ow To Run

- Activate the virtual environment and start the server:
  - Windows PowerShell:
    - .venv\Scripts\python app.py
  - Server runs at http://127.0.0.1:5000/
Verified Endpoints

- Health check: GET /health
  - Returns: {"status":"ok"}
- Login: POST /login with JSON body {"username":"admin","password":"password"}
  - Returns: {"access_token":"..."} — use this for Authorization: Bearer <token/>
- Create task: POST /tasks (JWT required)
  - Body: {"title":"Demo task","status":"pending"}
  - Returns created task with id/title/status
- List tasks: GET /tasks?page=1&limit=10 (JWT required)
  - Returns {"items":[...],"total":N}
- Non-JSON POSTs are rejected with 415 due to middleware.
- Invalid payloads on /tasks return 400 with validation details.
Integration Notes

- Base URL: http://127.0.0.1:5000
- Auth flow:
  - POST /login with credentials to get JWT
  - Include header Authorization: Bearer <token> for protected endpoints</token>
- CORS is enabled globally, so browser clients can call the API directly.
- Pagination params for /tasks: page (default 1), limit (default 10)
